This paper focuses on evaluating the importance of different network design choices and hyperparameters for sequence tagging tasks, which are commonly studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, which are often studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves optimization of hyperparameters, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves NLP tasks that often involve computer vision techniques, which are studied in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
